latestPosts.caption:
Second prize?
No — it was like first-class honour to hold my head high in front of decorated officers and speak my heart out on “Women in Fighting Arms as a Career.” Contesting at national levels with students of Amity University Noida, Chhattisgarh, and Haryana, wasn’t just a personal victory — it was a tribute to all the courageous and fearless women willing to serve their nation in uniform.

On #operationsindoor today on 7th may 2025, sitting here reminiscing about my days in the Manesar Military Camp, I am brimming with an ocean of pride deep inside me. I got to lead a soldier’s life - waking up at 5 in the morning, undergoing rigorous trainings, washing my own plate (all three meals, each day — no shortcuts!) and repeating it all again with discipline, dedication, and no excuses whatsoever. No comfort zones, no phones, no family — only the desire for excellence and the soldier’s spirit burning inside.

I was trained and mentored by the best war heroes - Colonel Ravinder Singh, Captain Satveer Singh Solanki, Captain Nayak Subedar Digambar Singh, and Captain Mahaveer Singh June, the Kargil War and URI surgical strike heroes. Learning from their real-life experiences was like having the pulse of history in one’s hand - raw, real, and so inspiring. what made it all the more beautiful was the sheer affection, respect, and admiration each and every individual around me had for me — from other cadets to senior officers

A nickname - “Kala Chashma.”
Not because of the shade, but because it reflected how i was seen - sharp, bold and full of life! Being regarded by these heroes as brave, strong, and courageous? That’s the sort of approval that no award can ever compete with.
This wasn’t just a second prize.
This was my badge of honour.
I showed up with heart — and left with a legacy.

#indianarmy #india #proudtobeindian #OperationSindoor #KalaChashma #WomenInUniform #LegacyInBoots #NotJustAPrize #ProudMoment
#militarycamp

Barefoot on soft grass, mangoes in hand, and heart full of beautiful emptiness 🧑‍🌾🌾days like this remind me where I truly belong.🏡There’s something so healing about being close to the land, feeling the stillness of nature🌴 that fills me more than anything ever could 🔱. It’s a return to what is actually real ⏳, to soul🪽 ,to self🪻. It’s more than just farming 🧚‍♂️— it’s coming home to yourself.🫀🫀🫀
